@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Daily Knowledge";
}

<header class="knowledge-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="badge fade-up" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">INSPIRATION</div>
            <h1 class="fade-up">Daily Islamic Knowledge</h1>
            <p class="fade-up">Start your day with a beautiful verse from the Quran, profound words from the Prophet (ﷺ), and inspiring daily supplications.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <section class="section-white" style="margin-top: -30px; position: relative; z-index: 10;">
        <div class="container">
            
            <!-- Verse of the Day -->
            <div class="knowledge-section fade-up">
                <div class="knowledge-section-header">
                    <h2><i class="ph-fill ph-book-open-text"></i> Verse of the Day</h2>
                    <a href="#" class="share-btn" onclick="event.preventDefault();"><i class="ph-bold ph-share-network"></i> Share</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="arabic-text" style="font-family: 'Amiri', serif;">
                    إِنَّ مَعَ الْعُسْرِ يُسْرًا
                </div>
                
                <div class="translation-text">
                    "Indeed, with hardship [will be] ease."
                </div>
                
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    This powerful verse reminds believers that no matter how difficult a situation may appear, Allah (SWT) always brings relief. It is repeated twice in Surah Ash-Sharh to emphasize certainty and provide immense comfort to the heart during challenging times.
                </div>
                
                <div class="reference-badge">Surah Ash-Sharh [94:6]</div>
            </div>

            <!-- Hadith of the Day -->
            <div class="knowledge-section fade-up" style="border-top-color: var(--secondary);">
                <div class="knowledge-section-header">
                    <h2 style="color: var(--secondary);"><i class="ph-fill ph-scroll"></i> Hadith of the Day</h2>
                    <a href="#" class="share-btn" onclick="event.preventDefault();"><i class="ph-bold ph-share-network"></i> Share</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="arabic-text" style="font-family: 'Amiri', serif;">
                    خَيْرُكُمْ مَنْ تَعَلَّمَ الْقُرْآنَ وَعَلَّمَهُ
                </div>
                
                <div class="translation-text">
                    The Prophet Muhammad (ﷺ) said: "The best among you (Muslims) are those who learn the Quran and teach it."
                </div>
                
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    Learning the Quran and imparting its knowledge to others is considered one of the highest acts of virtue in Islam. It ensures the preservation of divine guidance across generations.
                </div>
                
                <div class="reference-badge" style="background: #fcf4db; color: var(--secondary);">Sahih al-Bukhari 5027</div>
            </div>

            <!-- Grid for Dua, Quote, Reminder -->
            <div class="knowledge-grid fade-up">
                
                <!-- Daily Dua -->
                <div class="minimal-card">
                    <i class="ph-fill ph-hands-praying"></i>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: var(--text-main);">Daily Supplication</h3>
                    <div style="font-family: 'Amiri', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 15px; color: var(--primary);">
                        اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَسْأَلُكَ عِلْمًا نَافِعًا
                    </div>
                    <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">"O Allah, I ask You for beneficial knowledge."</p>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Islamic Quote -->
                <div class="minimal-card" style="background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                    <i class="ph-fill ph-quotes" style="color: var(--secondary);"></i>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 15px; color: var(--text-main);">Wisdom</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic; line-height: 1.6;">
                        "Knowledge enlivens the soul, illuminates the eyes, and brings light to the path."
                    </p>
                    <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--primary);">— Imam Al-Ghazali</p>
                </div>

            </div>

            <!-- Archive Section -->
            <div class="archive-section fade-up">
                <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 25px;"><i class="ph-bold ph-clock-counter-clockwise"></i> Previous Days</h2>
                
                <div class="archive-grid">
                    <div class="archive-card">
                        <h4>August 02, 2026</h4>
                        <p>Patience and Prayer (Surah Al-Baqarah 2:153)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="archive-card">
                        <h4>August 01, 2026</h4>
                        <p>The Value of Time (Surah Al-Asr 103:1-3)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="archive-card">
                        <h4>July 31, 2026</h4>
                        <p>Good Character (Hadith - Tirmidhi)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="archive-card">
                        <h4>July 30, 2026</h4>
                        <p>Trust in Allah (Surah At-Talaq 65:3)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->

<script>
        // Navbar Scroll Effect
        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            const navbar = document.querySelector('.navbar');
            if (window.scrollY > 10) {
                navbar.classList.add('scrolled');
            } else {
                navbar.classList.remove('scrolled');
            }
        });

        // Initialize Anime.js animations
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            anime({
                targets: '.fade-up',
                translateY: [30, 0],
                opacity: [0, 1],
                duration: 800,
                easing: 'easeOutCubic',
                delay: anime.stagger(100, {start: 100})
            });
        });
    </script>
